{
  "fileEdits": [
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "Same meter, new aisle.",
      "replace": "Same meter, different aisle.",
      "all": false
    },
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "Close the loop yourself before the next section: the meter has three readings worth knowing, positive, zero, and negative. State what each one says about two vectors, out loud or on paper, in your own words.",
      "replace": "The meter has three readings worth knowing: positive, zero, and negative. State what each one says about two vectors, out loud or on paper, in your own words.",
      "all": false
    },
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "Before you read on, take a guess: if you had to turn two lists of numbers into a single match score, what would you do to them?",
      "replace": "Take a guess before the next paragraph gives it away: if you had to turn two lists of numbers into a single match score, what would you do to them?",
      "all": false
    },
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "Before you read on, call it. Which candidate ends up with the highest score, and does any score go negative? Say an answer out loud.",
      "replace": "Stop and call it. Which candidate ends up with the highest score, and does any score go negative? Say an answer out loud.",
      "all": false
    },
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "We use tidy integers so your eyes can do the arithmetic the machine does silently.",
      "replace": "We use tidy integers so the reading stays clean while the machine does the same work silently.",
      "all": false
    },
    {
      "path": "doc/lesson.md",
      "find": "Next time the app hands you a stranger's song that is exactly right, you will know the number that said ship it, and you will know that number can be shouted over.",
      "replace": "Remember where we started: two lists of numbers got compared, and the comparison said same taste. Now you can run that comparison yourself. Next time the app hands you a stranger's song that is exactly right, you will know the number that said ship it, and you will know that number can be shouted over.",
      "all": false
    }
  ],
  "summary": "Renamed the beat-04 section header to 'Same meter, different aisle,' rewrote the section-3 closer to drop the redundant loop phrase without using 'one more,' varied two 'Before you read on' prediction frames, trimmed the eyes-do-arithmetic promise while keeping readability language, and added a recursive close mirroring beat-04b that loops back to the opening; the comma-splice sentence was not present in the doc target so no such edit was applied."
}

